## Problem

OpenCode server crashes silently - no logs exist to diagnose root cause. Investigation orch-go-r0s4m confirmed 5+ crashes but couldn't determine why.

## Implementation

Add to `~/Documents/personal/opencode/packages/opencode/src/server/server.ts`:

```javascript
process.on('uncaughtException', (err) => {
  const crash = {
    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
    type: 'uncaughtException',
    error: err.message,
    stack: err.stack,
    memory: process.memoryUsage()
  };
  fs.appendFileSync(
    path.join(os.homedir(), '.local/share/opencode/crash.log'),
    JSON.stringify(crash) + '\n'
  );
  process.exit(1);
});

process.on('unhandledRejection', (reason, promise) => {
  const crash = {
    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
    type: 'unhandledRejection',
    reason: String(reason),
    memory: process.memoryUsage()
  };
  fs.appendFileSync(
    path.join(os.homedir(), '.local/share/opencode/crash.log'),
    JSON.stringify(crash) + '\n'
  );
  process.exit(1);
});
```

## After Implementation

1. Rebuild: `cd ~/Documents/personal/opencode/packages/opencode && bun run build`
2. Restart: `orch-dashboard restart`
3. Next crash will produce log entry in `~/.local/share/opencode/crash.log`

## Success Criteria

- Crash log created on next OpenCode crash
- Log includes error, stack trace, and memory stats
- Can diagnose actual root cause from log

