## Context

Part of orch-go-9e15: Make headless spawn mode the default

## Task

Change the spawn command default behavior to use headless mode instead of tmux mode.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Default spawn behavior (no flags) uses runSpawnHeadless
- [ ] Add --tmux flag to enable tmux mode (opt-in)
- [ ] Remove --headless flag (no longer needed - it's the default)
- [ ] Maintain --inline flag for blocking TUI mode
- [ ] Update spawn command help text to reflect new default
- [ ] All tests pass

## Implementation Notes

File to modify: cmd/orch/main.go (around line 1031-1043)

Current logic:
```go
if inline {
    return runSpawnInline(...)
}
if headless {
    return runSpawnHeadless(...)
}
// Default: Tmux mode
return runSpawnTmux(...)
```

New logic:
```go
if inline {
    return runSpawnInline(...)
}
if tmux {
    return runSpawnTmux(...)
}
// Default: Headless mode
return runSpawnHeadless(...)
```

## Context

Part of cross-project daemon implementation. See parent investigation:
`.kb/investigations/2026-01-21-inv-cross-project-daemon-poll-multiple.md`

Depends on: orch-go-mdoob, orch-go-00zsx, orch-go-agukq

## Task

Modify daemon poll loop in `pkg/daemon/daemon.go` to iterate over projects when cross-project mode is enabled.

## Implementation

```go
func (d *Daemon) pollOnce() {
    if d.crossProject {
        projects, err := ListProjects()
        if err != nil {
            log.Printf("Failed to list projects: %v", err)
            return
        }

        for _, project := range projects {
            issues, err := ListReadyIssuesForProject(project.Path)
            if err != nil {
                log.Printf("[%s] Failed to list issues: %v", project.Name, err)
                continue  // Don't crash, continue to next project
            }

            for _, issue := range issues {
                if d.pool.TryAcquire() {
                    SpawnWorkForProject(issue.ID, project.Path)
                }
            }
        }
    } else {
        // Existing single-project logic
    }
}
```

## Key Points

- Error in one project should NOT block other projects
- Global capacity pool shared across all projects
- Include project name in log output: `[price-watch] Spawning pw-rqhl`
- Consider caching project list (refresh every N minutes, not every poll)

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Daemon iterates over all kb-registered projects when --cross-project enabled
- [ ] Single project error doesn't crash daemon or block others
- [ ] Capacity limit respected across all projects combined
- [ ] Log output includes project names for visibility

